race.comment: CRASH THE PARTY (3) ran the race of her life in the Magic Millions 3YO a fortnight ago, coming from last to be beaten just 1.4 lengths over 1400m. Looks perfectly placed now getting to the mile for the first time. Another run like the last one will see her grab an overdue win. Genuine colt WAR KING (4) had his first run over this distance last time out and did a good job to get up for second at this track. Draws better today and with that last run under his belt he can go one better. VERONA AFFAIR (11) led in a stark change of tactics last start and the gamble paid off, recording a narrow win at juicy odds over the mile at Doomben. Progressive filly who can now build on that performance. THE BEAR (1) was run off his legs over 1200m at the Sunshine Coast last Saturday. Capable of a far better run out to this trip. Last start Beaudesert winner NORTH POLE (2) will find this a lot harder but he might be worth including in the wider exotic bets at a price.
